The paper deals with coding theory over a finite field, which falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT). The study of error-correcting codes also has applications in cryptography (cs.CR). The paper discusses the structural properties of codes, which could be relevant to the design and analysis of algorithms (cs.DS). The use of polynomials and decomposition theorem suggests a connection to algebraic coding theory, which is a subfield of coding theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the use of an indeterminate, which could be relevant to the study of algebraic number theory and algebraic geometry, both of which have connections to computer science (cs.NI).
